municipal authorities. In promoting those services, people must learn how to 
draw the boundary-line between 'public' and 'private' in affairs of health to 
understand the importance of 'hygienic rules based on counsels for personal 
self-government', as Simon suggested 100 years ago, and health professionals 
must develop a public health system which depends not only on regulatory laws 
but also on scientific findings, as Rumsey advocated 150 years ago.

